<TEXT>
the left main gear on a delta 727 en route to 
atlanta collapsed wednesday as the plane was being towed away from 
an airport gate but officials said there were no injuries among 
the 121 people on board 
the aircraft pivoted down on the left side but the nose 
gear kept most of the plane upright said stapleton international 
airport spokesman norm avery 
the passengers and seven crew members deplaned through the 
jetway there was some damage to the left wingtip but a report of 
other damage was not immediately available he said 
the delta 727200 was scheduled to depart stapleton at 8 am 
on a nonstop flight to atlanta he said 
the aircraft had received authorization to be pushed back from 
its gate when the mishap occurred avery said 
