<TEXT>
since abbie hoffmans death last month 
his oldest son has been considering taking over the family 
business agitating 
andrew hoffman 28 has been living a quiet life here as a 
jeweler photographer sculptor and carpenter a selfdescribed 
blue collar jack of all trades 
but it might be time for a change 
so many people are wanting me to take on the family business 
but abbie did a lot of stuff and he had a lot of help he said 
were all feeling a void now before we didnt have to worry 
about it because abbie was out there doing it 
the younger hoffman has been collecting news clippings about his 
fathers death planning memorial services and other benefits 
he had never sought publicity but now hes trying to organize 
fundraisers in memory of his father to help causes that had been 
backed by the 60s radical 
andrew said his first thought after learning of his fathers 
death was that he had committed suicide although now he believes 
there are too many questions surrounding hoffmans death 
the elder hoffman was found dead in a bucks county pa 
apartment in march a medical examiner found he had taken 150 
phenobarbital tablets 
the last year or so he was depressed and he had tried 
suicide before andrew hoffman said but he wasnt depressed in 
the same way he was not suicidal the last conversation i had with 
him was very upbeat 
andrew and his sister ilya are the offspring of hoffmans first 
marriage which ended in 1966 
hoffman left his entire estate to his longtime companion johanna 
lawrenson in a 1983 letter to his children unsealed after his 
death hoffman tried to explain his will 
i felt what he really meant was that we should carry on to do 
what we find best to do in our hearts by not leaving us anything 
monetary he was saying you have my blood and my spirit and you 
can do great things in this world if you just fight on andrew 
hoffman said 
thats basically what im trying to do 
</TEXT>
