the congress of peoples deputies is new but the 
method of counting votes is as old as communist rule 
president mikhail s gorbachev presiding over the initial 
debate and several procedural votes at todays inaugural session of 
the 2250member body promised to speed up the process but not 
in time for this session 
since the communists came to power in 1917 balloting has been 
by show of hands at party meetings delegates traditionally raise 
their party cards members of the legislature the supreme soviet 
vote with a forest of hands 
by custom such votes simply endorse the decisions of the 
leadership making precise counts unnecessary 
the tradition started to falter only within the last year 
but as wrangling broke out today at the start of the 
longawaited session of the countrys first competitively elected 
congress it became apparent the old way would be quite 
timeconsuming 
opposition to the leadership emerged even on procedural 
questions 
who is for this agenda gorbachev asked as the body 
considered the plan adopted by a closed caucus wednesday night 
most of the 2155 deputies present raised their delegate cards 
who is against he asked when only a smattering of cards 
appeared in the cavernous auditorium gorbachev began counting 
aloud he gave up when he reached 31 and asked for an official 
count 
a 10minute pause ensued as representatives of each sector in 
the hall counted votes by hand the tally was 379 against with nine 
abstentions 
gorbachev declared the agenda adopted but there was grumbling 
among the deputies and he called for another show of hands of those 
opposed 
do not get excited he said i know what to do i can see 
that this is the minority i think we are not going to count this 
time there is an absolute majority the agenda is adopted 
after several more vote counts the president told the delegates 
that an electronic counting system would be installed 
soon he said very soon 
