the ss23 missiles which have a range of about 315 miles or 
just above the treaty threshold were outlawed along with all us 
and soviet missiles with a range of 312 to 3125 miles 
soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze said may 13 while 
on a trip to west germany that destruction of the ss23s might be 
stopped if the north atlantic treaty organization deployed new 
lance missiles 
the usbuilt lances have a range of about 75 miles but after 
the treaty was signed the united states and britain launched a 
campaign within nato to more than triple the missiles range to 
just below 300 miles 
west germany and several smaller countries in the western 
alliance registered objections to the modernization program and 
called for ussoviet negotiations over the lances and other 
shortrange nuclear arms 
