out official county business 
state law requires each county with more than 30000 people to 
have at least four justice of the peace precincts each with a 
constable and a justice ellis countys population is estimated at 
75000 
a constable like a sheriff is an elected official and a 
certified peace officer authorized to carry a gun make arrests and 
serve courtrelated documents 
in urban counties constables usually serve notices of lawsuits 
and other papers associated with the civil court system they also 
serve as bailiffs in the justice of the peace courts while the 
sheriff runs the jail and carries out law enforcement functions 
each of dallas countys eight constables is paid 49152 
annually plus a monthly car allowance of 350 
but in rural counties the sheriff is responsible for all jail 
and courtrelated activities and the constables office is largely 
symbolic 
