than previously believed was most responsible for the downward 
revision in the firstquarter gnp 
the smaller inventory list was seen as a plus for the economy 
because large buildups without accompanying sales often mean job 
layoffs 
and the increased exports combined with fewer imports resulted 
in a betterthanexpected decline in the trade deficit the report 
said the deficit narrowed at an annual rate of 176 billion the 
first improvement since the spring of 1988 exports in the 
januarymarch quarter rose at a 153 percent annual rate compared 
with a 09 percent increase in imports 
