tap a rhythmic art that blends african dance with the irish jig 
and lively english clog originated among black dancers performing 
on street corners and in saloons 
unlike ballet dancers tap dancers hold their body limp like a 
rag doll and use the natural movements to belt out rhythms with 
their feet 
