<TEXT>
the new parliament on thursday reaffirmed its 
predecessors choice of mikhail gorbachev as president in a session 
marked by unprecedented debate and tough questioning of a soviet 
leader 
gorbachev won more than 95 percent of the vote in uncontested 
balloting at the opening session of the congress of peoples 
deputies the first competitively chosen soviet parliament 
maverick communist boris n yeltsin withdrew his name before the 
vote and the new parliament rejected a member who tried to 
nominate himself 
although opponents of the established leadership were a distinct 
minority the combative atmosphere contrasted sharply with that of 
previous soviet parliaments that rubberstampedthe actions of the 
kremlin leadership 
gorbachev received 2123 of the 2210 votes cast yuri a 
osipyan chairman of the commission that counted the ballots 
announced during the nationally televised proceedings eightyseven 
deputies voted against the communist party chief osipyan said and 
11 abstained 
gorbachev who has led the soviet union since 1985 had been 
elected president on oct 1 by the congress predecessor the 
supreme soviet he succeeded andrei a gromyko in what was then a 
largely ceremonial post 
in the new governmental structure the fiveyear presidency is 
to be invested with greater powers including the chairmanship of 
the defense council and the right to propose laws and negotiate 
with foreign powers 
in a clear reference to past soviet dictatorships gorbachev 
vowed to pursue the line of democracy until the very end so that 
what has happened in this country will never again be repeated 
communist party ideology chief vadim a medvedev told reporters 
the partys victory in nationwide balloting in march entitled it to 
pick its leader as president 
the party went through the election process it won support 
therefore the socalled cabinet will be formed from its leaders 
medvedev said 
one deputy sought to nominate yeltsin to run against gorbachev 
