japan lashed out at the united states friday for 
targeting japanese trade barriers under a us trade law that could 
lead to stiff tariffs on japanese exports to its biggest market 
foreign minister sousuke uno called the action extremely 
regrettable 
he said it was unfair because the united states has 
unilaterally made such a decision on the trade practices of other 
countries including japan despite the fact that the us itself 
maintains import restrictive measures and practices to a 
considerable degree 
the foreign minister urged the united states to reduce its 
huge budget deficit he said the socalled super 301 list 
of unfair trade practices was an attempt to divert attention from 
the major cause of the trade imbalance between the two countries 
and to deny us responsibility for faltering economic policies 
as a result of many marketopening measures which have been 
taken to date the japanese market has now become a widely open 
market uno said none of the identified priority practices 
can be considered to constitute trade barriers 
the bush administration announced thursday it had named trade 
barriers in japan brazil and india under its massive trade law 
enacted last year us trade representative carla hills said the 
administration will immediately begin negotiations with the three 
countries to try to get the barriers removed so that any threatened 
us trade sanctions would be unnecessary 
if the talks are unsuccessful the us government can levy 
tariffs of up to 100 percent against selected imports from an 
offending country 
mrs hills who made the announcement in washington cited japan 
for refusal to buy americanmade satellites and supercomputers as 
well as its barriers on us lumber products 
this framework by which the united states forces us to 
negotiate by selfishly imposing sanctions violates the fundamental 
idea of multilateral trade negotitions under the general 
agreement on tariffs and trade or gatt said hiroshi mitsuzuka 
japans minister of international trade and industry 
we will raise this issue at mutinational meetings mitsuzuka 
added 
