yields on twoyear treasury notes fell to the 
lowest level since last october 
the average yield in the governments auction wednesday was 884 
percent down from 934 percent at the last auction on april 26 
it was the lowest rate since twoyear notes averaged 833 
percent on oct 26 1988 the notes will carry a coupon interest 
rate of 8 percent with each 10000 in face value selling for 
998380 
a total of 877 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling 
2778 billion 
