<TEXT>
nintendo co ltd spent most of its 100year 
history producing playing cards with the cherry blossoms and cranes 
of traditional japan now its trump card is a modern computer game 
that is the bestselling toy in the united states 
the top japanese maker of home computer video games reported 
17 billion in us sales in 1988 alone and is believed to have at 
least a 75 percent hold on the american market for the hightech 
toys 
nec home electronics a us subsidiary of japanese computer and 
telecommunications giant nec announced last tuesday it has devised 
a superior home video game system that will go on sale in the 
united states this fall but nintendo executives say theyre not 
worried 
for nearly a century nintendo was literally a house of cards 
until the 1970s its main products were playing cards for a 
traditonal japanese game called hanafuda as well as ones used in 
western card games 
in the 1980s the company of 690 employees nestled in a green 
valley in japans ancient capital kyoto began making toys with 
audio visual features using microcomputers last year only three 
years after introducing its games in the united states the 
nintendo entertainment system nes was the no 1selling toy 
there according to toy and hobby world magazine 
