computer games in both countries and imanishi says 95 percent of 
the companys efforts are channeled into developing new games for 
the console but the company is not worried that its explosive 
success could fizzle 
we are creating entertainment and that is a timeless concept 
that doesnt change imanishi said 
for the future nintendo is developing software that will allow 
its computer console owners to trade stocks and do their banking at 
home they are also seeking ways to appeal to consumers beyond the 
10 to 17yearold males who are now their biggest customers 
