<TEXT>
two general motors corp carmaking divisions on 
thursday adjusted their incentive packages by adding some vehicles 
boosting the incentives on others and cutting back rebates on a few 
models 
the new incentives announced by the pontiac and chevrolet 
divisions run through july 10 
incentives are used by automakers to help sell models that 
arent selling as fast as they hope 
on march 30 gm announced a wideranging package of incentives 
for many of its cars and light trucks that package was to expire 
on june 5 
that announcement came the day after ford motor co kicked off 
the latest round of incentive frenzy with a program that gave 
buyers the option of cash rebates or financing with interest rates 
as low as 29 percent 
that program is scheduled to end wednesday ford spokesman bill 
carroll said earlier this week he expected the company to make an 
announcement then that it was extending some form of incentives 
chrysler corp followed its larger cousins lead in early april 
and offered interestfree financing on some loans as an option to 
cash rebates the chrysler program has no expiration date 
