<TEXT>
the sale of eastern airlines northeast shuttle 
business to developer donald trump marks a critical juncture in 
easterns 2month path through a bruising strike and complex 
bankruptcy proceeding 
the 365 million sale to trump was approved formally thursday by 
us bankruptcy judge burton r lifland following eight months 
that saw court challenges to the deal by easterns unions and by a 
rival suitor 
the sale of the new yorkwashingtonboston shuttle means eastern 
wont be sold in its entirety a key goal of the airlines unions 
miamibased eastern filed for chapter 11 protection from its 
creditors march 9 five days after the start of a strike by 
machinists that has been supported by pilots and flight attendants 
and has forced a sharp curtailing of easterns flights 
the unions have vowed not to end their strike until the airline 
was sold or otherwise taken from the control of frank lorenzo 
chairman of easterns parent texas air corp 
the company has received several buyout proposals including a 
464 million plan from a group led by former baseball commissioner 
peter ueberroth but has not accepted any as viable 
in recent weeks easterns unions have had intensive discussions 
with investor groups interested in buying all of eastern two of 
those groups one headed by former piedmont airlines chairman 
william howard and the other by chicago commodities trader joseph 
ritchie have submitted formal bids to the bankruptcy court which 
must approve any sale of eastern or its assets 
david i shapiro the courtappointed examiner for eastern has 
dismissed those offers as not viable and challenged potential 
suitors to include at least 100 million in cash toward the 
purchase 
lorenzo has said the shuttle sale would give momentum to his own 
plan to rebuild eastern as a smaller carrier and sell another 14 
billion or so worth of eastern assets the bankruptcy court has not 
yet passed judgment on that plan although eastern has been making 
deals for the sale of aircraft landing slots and other assets in 
the event it is approved 
eastern also has been hiring and training new pilots to replace 
the strikers and says it plans to have enough when combined with 
pilots it expects to cross picket lines to meet the needs of the 
smaller carrier 
</TEXT>
