general motors corp said thursday it is 
extending a fiveyear 50000mile warranty on frontwheeldrive 
power steering assemblies to cars made between 1985 and 1988 
gm said the systems may fail to work properly shortly after the 
engine is started in cold weather 
in january 1988 gm announced a fiveyear 50000mile power 
steering warranty on frontwheeldrive cars made between 1982 and 
1985 
but the washingtonbased center for auto safety said it was 
disappointed that gm did not plan to notify consumers directly 
about the problem the consumer advocacy group unsuccessfully 
petitioned for a recall of the cars in 1986 
people in this situation may be spending 500 or 600 for 
repair needlessly said the centers russell shew 
gm said it would reimburse owners who paid to have the problem 
corrected within the fiveyear or 50000mile limit if those cars 
were not eligible for the coverage now 
